"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-simone-biles-vault-olympic-practice\", \"text\": \"Simone Biles is back for her third Olympicsin Paris and it looks like she's more than ready to show everyone why she is considered the GOAT of a sport that will likely once again be one of the biggest draws of the Summer Games.  Biles and the rest of the U.S. women's gymnastics team ran through a practice session on Thursday, with events kicking off Sunday and being held almost every day next week. Cameras caught Biles, who pulled herself out of the team finals at the Tokyo Games in 2021 to focus on her mental health, pulling off a sweet move on the vault.  Check this out:  HERE IT IS!!!!https://t.co/S3uuNBGUs7  Biles already looks locked in, which is great news for Team USA.  Fans loved seeing it:  Simone is ready.https://t.co/yrEZ2MLKa4  The only perk to a 4:58 a.m. wake up call from my 2.5 year old. DAAANNNNGGGGGhttps://t.co/wDSIRWOFAm  She is everything.Hope she's feeling as great as she appears to!https://t.co/bJA0aGEOIE  I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve watched this at least 10 times now on repeat.https://t.co/nBpDgEo3gI  I could literally watch@Simone_Bilesall day. \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u008dhttps://t.co/Qn2AjntTSM  the way I have watched this on repeathttps://t.co/i5V2EuMiET  Andy Nesbitt is the assistant managing editor of audience engagement at Sports Illustrated. He works closely with the Breaking and Trending News team to shape SI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s daily coverage across all sports. A 20-year veteran of the sports media business, he has worked for Fox Sports, For the Win, The Boston Globe and NBC Sports, having joined SI in February 2023. Nesbitt is a golf fanatic who desperately wants to see the Super Bowl played on a Saturday night.  Follow anezbitt  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2025ABG-SI LLC- SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended